12. Real SRE Interview Scenarios (What Companies Actually Ask)

These are not theoretical — these are real patterns used in interviews.

12.1 Scenario: Service Down (Critical Incident)
Problem:

Production web service is down.

What interviewer expects:
Detection
Diagnosis
Mitigation
Prevention
Script (Auto-Healing + Logging)
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

SERVICE="httpd"
LOG="/var/log/service_monitor.log"

log() {
  echo "$(date '+%F %T') $1" | tee -a "$LOG"
}

if ! systemctl is-active --quiet "$SERVICE"; then
  log "ERROR: $SERVICE is down. Restarting..."
  systemctl restart "$SERVICE"

  if systemctl is-active --quiet "$SERVICE"; then
    log "INFO: $SERVICE restarted successfully"
  else
    log "CRITICAL: Failed to restart $SERVICE"
  fi
else
  log "INFO: $SERVICE is running"
fi
What you should SAY in interview:
“This is auto-healing”
“Includes observability via logs”
“Could integrate with alerting system”
12.2 Scenario: High Disk Usage
Problem:

Disk reaches 95% → system crashes

Script
THRESHOLD=85

df -h | awk 'NR>1 {print $5,$6}' | while read usage mount; do
  value=$(echo $usage | cut -d'%' -f1)

  if [ "$value" -ge "$THRESHOLD" ]; then
    echo "WARNING: $mount at $value%"
  fi
done
Expected Answer:
Detect early
Alert
Optionally clean logs automatically
